1
00:00:00,541 --> 00:00:04,041
Here on this door they used to
shackle the prisoners

2
00:00:04,791 --> 00:00:07,208
We could not see them but we spoke
to them from under the door

3
00:00:07,916 --> 00:00:10,458
A friend of ours was also shackled
here, we used to talk to him

4
00:00:10,708 --> 00:00:12,500
Interviewer: Can you
mention his name?

5
00:00:12,541 --> 00:00:16,958
The young man's name was Abboud, he was
from our area, from the town of Tabqa

6
00:00:18,125 --> 00:00:19,416
I kept talking to him

7
00:00:19,666 --> 00:00:22,166
Even when the jailer came he would ask
him: Abboud, does your hand hurt?

8
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:22,875
He would say yes

9
00:00:23,375 --> 00:00:26,833
Then he would tighten the handcuffs
until Abboud screamed in pain

10
00:00:27,666 --> 00:00:31,083
Of course Abboud was suspended from the door because
of the blindfold incident in the interrogation room

11
00:00:32,458 --> 00:00:33,708
Interviewer: Where was
the interrogation room?

12
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:35,083
The interrogation room is here

13
00:00:36,375 --> 00:00:39,458
Of course there was a cinder block wall here dividing
the room, with a black door in it

14
00:00:41,208 --> 00:00:45,291
From the moment you enter you take
off your shoes because of the carpet

15
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,166
You enter here and he would
be sitting like this

16
00:00:48,875 --> 00:00:49,875
Sitting here

17
00:00:50,541 --> 00:00:52,833
Of course it was laid out with
Gulf-style carpet and mattresses

18
00:00:52,916 --> 00:00:56,166
From under the blindfold I could
see the color of the carpet

19
00:00:57,916 --> 00:01:00,583
You sit kneeling with your
hands cuffed behind your back

20
00:01:01,875 --> 00:01:03,125
He starts asking questions
and you answer them

21
00:01:04,625 --> 00:01:07,333
Whatever question he asks
you must answer

22
00:01:08,916 --> 00:01:14,375
Interviewer: Did they beat or torture you
in the interrogation room? How did they torture you?

23
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:21,083
They would sit you here with one person standing
behind you and another from this direction

24
00:01:22,208 --> 00:01:23,625
Then you hear the sound of
a pistol being loaded

25
00:01:25,166 --> 00:01:26,291
He tells the one holding the
pistol: finish him off

26
00:01:28,083 --> 00:01:32,041
Then he runs his hand like this
past your ear

27
00:01:32,500 --> 00:01:35,000
He keeps circling around you while the
other one strikes you with the hammer

28
00:01:35,291 --> 00:01:37,166
Or with the <i>Lakhdar Brahimi</i>
hose on your knees or feet

29
00:01:38,875 --> 00:01:43,208
Interviewer: What are the names of the torture
instruments you were tortured with or heard of?

30
00:01:44,291 --> 00:01:48,958
There was the hammer,
I will never forget it

31
00:01:50,916 --> 00:01:53,041
And the <i>Lakhdar Brahimi</i>
hose, it is well known

32
00:01:54,791 --> 00:01:56,083
And there was the <i>balingo</i>
[hoist] for suspending prisoners

33
00:01:56,083 --> 00:01:57,416
And here there was <i>shabeh</i>
[suspension] on the door

34
00:01:58,458 --> 00:02:03,166
They suspended people, we heard their
screaming but we did not know who they were

35
00:02:03,916 --> 00:02:05,500
Those we did not know,
we could not talk to them

